1 November 2015 On Tuesday, 03 November at 12h30, The Minister of Trade and Industry Dr Rob Davies will brief the media on the African Growth and Opportunity Act (AGOA). The briefing will be held at Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town with a video link up to Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria.On Thursday, 05 November at 10h00, The Minister in the Presidency for Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation Jeff Radebe will address media on the outcome of the Cabinet meeting to be held on Wednesday, 04 November 2015. Full details will be communicated through a media advisory during the week.On Thursday, 05 November at 12h00, The Minister of Health Dr Aaron Motsoaledi will be releasing the investigation report into the Health Profession Council of South Africa. The briefing will be held at Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria with a video link up to Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town.In addition to these media briefings, Ministers participate in various public events. For a comprehensive list of national and provincial government activities visit www.gov.za.Should there be changes in the information above, members of the media will be notified accordingly.Enquiries: Themba Sepotokele Cell: 082 490 9869Issued by Government Communication and Information System